<Content>Worst hotel ever visited DO NOT GO TO THIS HOTEL!!!!!!!First of all their website is A LIE! Don't believe anything on there.The place is a total dump. We thought it would be a cool old hotel, and it was old for sure. Our Junior Suite was smaller than most regular hotel rooms I have stayed in and completely filthy. The carpet used to be red (from the looks of it under the pink couch which used to be red as well) but was brown throughout the room. The television (at least 20 years old) didn't work, and the mini fridge was older than the TV. We had to wait over an hour to check in and the staff was unhelpful to say the least. The clawfooted tub we were promised was nowhere to be found in the world's-smallest-bathroom (you had to press up against the shower to close the door, which was necessary to get into the toilet and sink). No air conditioning, room smelled funny and I don't think the cover on the bed has been changed since the day the hotel opened. We had a room on the top floor and it was SO loud from the street all night.The restaurant was nice for dinner (the only reason they get 1 star) but when we went down for breakfast (1.5 hrs after it was supposed to begin) we were told that the restaurant wasn't open yet because the chef hadn't shown up. Then the kicker- when we checked out (after paying for the $20 valet charge) our car pulled up and had a HUGE dent in the side!! If that wasn't bad enough, while we were filling out the accident report, their brilliant valet decides to re-park a car infront of ours and smashes into our bumper and the bumper of the car in front of him!!!!!! All in all, it was the worst hotel experience we have ever had (and traveling with sports teams, I have stayed in some pretty budget hotels) and I wouldn't pay $50 for a room there, much less $200.Even the staff knows it is terrible, and according to them, it is getting worse with the new manager they have. The saving grace of the hotel is the young girl who works at the front