<Author>csg
<Content>Lovely, unique, old hotel My son, his friend, and I recently spent three nights in two rooms at Hotel Majestic. My first impression in the lobby was one of dark elegance with lovely fabrics, sofas, etc. There was free computer in the lobby with a printer (15 page limit), so that made it easy to print out boarding passes the day before we left San Francisco. My son's room had a canopy bed and a very large bathroom with an antique footed tub. They were in room 410. Because of the ghost rumors about the 4th floor, I requested another floor and was given room 200 at the top of the first flight of stairs. My room was lovely, but it was much smaller with a tiny bathroom. It was fine since I was alone, but it might have been a bit crowded if my husband had been with me. The floors sloped and creaked a lot, but I was aware that this building is over 100 years old, so I didn't mind. The tv in my room was so old, it was really funny! It did have remote control, but it really looked like something out of the 70's or early 80's. The restaurant was very highly rated, but we only had breakfast there, which was good. We paid $160 per night per room, so that was cheap by San Francisco standards. I think it is cheaper because of the location. It's almost isolated. There was, however, an Episcopal church just around the corner which I was able to attend on Sunday morning without calling a cab. Otherwise, we cabbed it to everywhere. Overall, it was a nice hotel at a good price, but you should know in advance that it is OLD. 
