<Content>Not bad for a hundred or so years old! The Hotel Majestic is a nice choice for anyone looking for a relatively enjoyable and quick stay in San Francisco. Their rooms have lovely beds, often with a canopy, which I have never seen in a hotel before. It is slightly odd, but adds to the nice feel of the hotel and besides, it's so comfortable! The service is nice, but we did not ask for too much from them...we are not luxury travelers.The cons are not plentiful, but they are definitely there. I understand that they have tried to preserve the old, quaint, character of the hotel. This was mostly successful, but our bathtub was old and slightly awkward. It is very old-fashioned, with claw foots, and the hotel appears to be proud of having them. I suppose that it is impressive to have them functioning after all these years, but it is actually almost dangerous to get out of the bathtub because of its height. I don't know if all the rooms had these awkward and rather unsightly bathtubs, but we were taken aback. We got used to it after one night, but it was strange.The carpeting was kinda old, but we weren't expecting the Park Hyatt Chicago or anything. The armoire was quite creepy - nice but creepy. An added plus was the decorative fireplace. It was quite beautiful and definitely the cleanest thing in the room - very polished and shiny. Shiny is always nice for a traveler...Overall, we had a nice stay, but I wish Tripadvisor had a three-and-a-half star rating. I would award this hotel with it if it existed. 
