<Content>Fantastic hotel, fantastic location Myself and my wife stayed at the majestic for a few days as part of our honeymoon recently. We had come from a plush 5-star hotel in Cabo San Lucas, and were heading on to Chain hotels in Vegas  L.A., so I wanted something a little different for our stay in S.F.The hotel is superbly located, between the cool, chic boutiques and restaurants of Fillmore street and the typical mayhem of downtown. I have to agree with everything the previous reviewer said, so instead of going into detail here, you should read the review by hawaiilover. The staff were extremely courteous and helpful, the rooms were huge (we also had a one0bedroom suite on the 4th floor), and the service was excellent. Our only slightly negative thought on this hotel is that, as the building is so old, the walls in the rooms aren't very well sound-proofed. We found each morning that we were woken by people walking up and down the corridor outside the room. It wasn't particularly early, but I suppose you always want to wake up in your own time rather than be woken up by others.All-in-all, this is a fantastic hotel, with great staff and great rates. I believe the hotel was taken over by new owners last year, who have changed the bar and restaurant. They must have changed the attitude of the staff as well, as we encountered no negativity at all during our stay. Just like the previous reviewer, if I'm ever back in San Francisco, I won't even bother to look around for other hotels, this one is ideal. 
